### Diagnostics

- `health_check`: read-only. Reports configuration and which tool categories are enabled. Call this first when any tool returns an error.

## Setup

Provider wiring and the MCP registration steps are documented in `docs/integrations/SETUP.md`. Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and fill in the placeholders for the categories you enabled.

## Register the server

Add {{ASSISTANT_NAME}} to your host config (for Claude Code, `~/.claude.json`):

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "{{ASSISTANT_SLUG}}": {
      "command": "uv",
      "args": [
        "run",
        "--directory",
        "/absolute/path/to/{{ASSISTANT_SLUG}}",
        "{{ASSISTANT_SLUG}}-mcp"
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

## Running locally

```bash
uv run {{ASSISTANT_SLUG}}-mcp
```

This starts the MCP server on stdio. Once it is running, call `health_check` to confirm configuration.

## Tests and static checks

```bash
uv run python -m unittest discover -s tests
uv run python -m compileall -q {{ASSISTANT_SLUG}}
```

